{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01ACvHmrB9CNuJP2WbfMxt4N","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t<!-- chosen: TL1 -->\n2\t<!-- punchline: Δ*fur* derepression is the demonstrable driver of the lipid A-loss-permissive envelope state, and everything downstream is the supporting (and still-open) mechanism it sets in motion. -->\n3\t\n4\t# Throughline (chosen: TL1)\n5\t\n6\t_Picked from `00_throughline_candidates.md` by the smoke orchestrator's throughline gate._\n7\t\n8\t---\n9\t\n10\t## Candidate TL1: Δ*fur* derepression is the demonstrable driver of the lipid A-loss-permissive envelope state, and everything downstream is the supporting (and still-open) mechanism it sets in motion.\n11\t\n12\t**Evidence map:**\n13\t\n14\t| Sub-claim | Source | Strength |\n15\t|---|---|---|\n16\t| A1 — Δ*fur* derepression is a major driver (Spearman ρ=0.315, p=2.08e-03, 71% sign concordance over 93 Leaden DEGs) | REPORT §\"Finding 1\"; nb 01_leaden2018_fur_signature.ipynb cell 5 | ✓ direct |\n17\t| A2 — signal is constitutive Δ*fur* derepression, not an iron-limitation response | REPORT §\"Finding 1\"; nb 01 cell 7 | ⚠ partial — single growth condition (PYE rich) |\n18\t| A3 — cbb3/*fix* respiratory operon is the Fur-released listing buffered by Δ*sspB* | REPORT §\"Finding 1\"; nb 01 cell 9 | ◇ orthogonal — concerns the SspB arm, not the Fur-driver claim |\n19\t| A4 — Path A (32 Fur-released genes) enriched for envelope-stress fitness (17/32=53.1%, fold 1.60×, p=0.016) | REPORT §\"Finding 2\"; nb 02b_h2_hypergeometric_verdict.ipynb cell 2 | ⚠ partial — marginal enrichment above 33.25% background |\n20\t| A5 — genome-background calibration (K=1311/N=3943=33.25%) underpinning the test | REPORT §\"Finding 2\"; nb 02b cell 1 | ✓ direct |\n21\t| A6 — ≥10% threshold miscalibration lesson | REPORT §Results scorecard; RESEARCH_PLAN §thresholds | ◇ orthogonal — methodological, not biology |\n22\t| A7 — SspB-buffered respiratory arm (Path B) is mechanistically critical | REPORT §\"Finding 2\"; nb 02b cell 2 | ✗ contradicts — 9/26=34.6%, fold 1.04×, p=0.515 (background); narrows the driver to Fur alone |\n23\t| A8 — ChvI two-phase partition (20 early / 10 both / 49 late) | REPORT §\"Finding 3\"; nb 03_chvi_phase_partition_sigU.ipynb cell 7 | ⚠ partial — downstream consequence of the Fur-set envelope state |\n24\t| A9 — ChvI autoregulation (CCNA_00237 +1.45) | REPORT §\"Finding 3\"; nb 03 cell 7 | ◇ orthogonal — downstream regulatory detail |\n25\t| A10 — SigU drives the late ChvI cohort | REPORT §\"Finding 3\"; nb 03 cell 10 | ✗ contradicts — 24.5% coherence, Fisher p=0.243 |\n26\t| A11 — ChvR sRNA post-transcriptional confound | ADVERSARIAL_REVIEW_2 N3 | ◇ orthogonal — confound to acknowledge |\n27\t| A12 — sphingolipid biosynthesis constitutive, not induced | REPORT §\"Finding 4\"; nb 04_sphingolipid_lpt_panel.ipynb cell 4 | ◇ orthogonal — context for the rescued state, not the Fur-driver claim |\n28\t| A13 — CtpA as LpxF-equivalent processing step | REPORT §\"Finding 4\"; nb 04 cell 5 | ✗ contradicts — REJECTED at pre-registered bar |\n29\t| A14 — Lpt apparatus repurposed for sphingolipid transport | REPORT §\"Finding 4\"; nb 04 cells 4 & 6 | ⚠ partial — transcript-protein discordance |\n30\t| A15 — OM proteome direction-only (single replicate) | REPORT §\"Finding 4\"; nb 04 cell 6 | ⚠ partial |\n31\t| A16 — *lptC2* single-replicate protein increase | REPORT §\"Finding 4\"; nb 04 cell 6 | ◇ orthogonal — pilot, appendix |\n32\t| A17 — *sphk* present in *A. baumannii* (scope note) | ADVERSARIAL_REVIEW_2 N1 | ◇ orthogonal |\n33\t| A18 — PG specific lytic engagement (SdpA +4.8; Pal +2.08/+2.84) | REPORT §\"Finding 5\"; nb 05_pg_remodeling.ipynb cell 5 | ◇ orthogonal — downstream envelope response |\n34\t| A19 — PG broad basal shutdown (28 loci, 20 DOWN) | REPORT §\"Finding 5\"; nb 05 cell 5 | ◇ orthogonal |\n35\t| A20 — PG protein-level statistics caveat | REPORT §\"Finding 5\"; nb 05 cell 6 | ⚠ partial |\n36\t| A21 —